00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:23.260
Later on, sync came along and gave you the ability to kind
of get that information across all the different computers

00:01:23.260 --> 00:01:28.620
that you own, but again it was still kind of
geared at your personal calendaring information.

00:01:30.189 --> 00:01:36.259
Then we shifted to iCal version 2 and iCal version 2 added
something a little more interesting which was published

00:01:36.260 --> 00:01:43.570
and subscribed over WebDAV, and that gave you the ability to
share a calendar with other people in a read-only fashion,

00:01:43.569 --> 00:01:49.719
